12:40.240 --> 12:41.560
But she's with Martin.

12:43.680 --> 12:44.680
You didn't know?

12:46.000 --> 12:48.160
How do you mean?

12:49.800 --> 12:52.040
-You know, "with."
-"With"?

12:54.320 --> 12:58.840
-Hey, that's okay.
-Sure, I just thought you...

12:59.480 --> 13:00.520
What?

13:01.440 --> 13:03.520
-You thought that I what?
-Nothing.

13:04.760 --> 13:07.280
-Look, just put on your shirt.
-Yes.

13:14.480 --> 13:16.360
-Let me see that.
-Ouch, damn it.

13:16.440 --> 13:20.560
It's infected. We need a doctor.
It needs to be cleaned.

14:27.240 --> 14:29.320
You're not eating their food, are you?

14:29.400 --> 14:30.600
Yes, we are, Martin.

14:33.760 --> 14:36.040
-Who are you?
-Martin.

14:36.480 --> 14:39.600
What is this place?
How can you have vegetables and bread?

14:39.680 --> 14:42.840
Shut the fuck up.
They're just trying to be here.

14:42.920 --> 14:46.440
I found children's shoes.
See any children here?

14:46.880 --> 14:49.160
-They must have grown up or...
-Or what?

14:49.720 --> 14:52.840
What do you mean?
They're right outside, playing.

14:58.720 --> 15:00.320
You're interrupting their meal.

15:01.680 --> 15:04.320
And we don't wear our old clothes here.

15:04.800 --> 15:07.880
What's the deal with these hippie duds?

15:08.560 --> 15:10.680
Are you some sort of cult?

15:10.920 --> 15:15.160
I understand your doubts,
your questions...

15:15.840 --> 15:18.560
your distrust towards others.

15:19.440 --> 15:24.080
I, too, have had that nagging doubt.

15:25.280 --> 15:31.040
Who can I believe?
Can I trust anyone out there?

15:34.960 --> 15:37.520
But we've done away
with those doubts here.

15:37.600 --> 15:39.640
Just like that?

15:39.720 --> 15:41.160
How did you do that?

15:42.200 --> 15:44.960
By melting into one.

15:46.560 --> 15:51.280
It all boils down to:
what do I fear if I don't exist?

15:52.480 --> 15:54.440
We are one, and we are now.

15:55.280 --> 15:57.240
That's all that matters.

15:58.520 --> 16:00.800
-Is it good?
-It's delicious.

16:01.040 --> 16:02.960
Good. Dig in.

16:04.320 --> 16:07.480
We have no past, no name, no gender.

16:09.880 --> 16:12.840
It's the end of the world,
but we're right here,

16:12.920 --> 16:17.000
right now, and that's all that matters.

16:19.800 --> 16:21.920
Do you even hear what you're saying?

16:22.400 --> 16:24.360
That's the dumbest thing I ever heard.

16:25.600 --> 16:27.280
Calm down, Martin.

16:30.360 --> 16:32.840
They're trying to help us.

16:40.200 --> 16:42.920
I apologize for Martin, our friend.

16:44.160 --> 16:46.560
He means well.

16:48.560 --> 16:55.480
Some people react with fright
at all the love here.

16:58.160 --> 16:59.600
We're not so used to it.

17:01.240 --> 17:02.080
Love.

17:05.079 --> 17:06.760
You can stay if you want to.

17:08.400 --> 17:10.640
Settle down and become one of us.

17:11.160 --> 17:12.760
I think we have to move on.

17:14.720 --> 17:16.960
Our monthly celebration is tomorrow.

17:17.640 --> 17:18.760
What's that?

17:18.839 --> 17:22.359
Once a month, we share a nice meal...

17:23.359 --> 17:26.920
in silence and gratitude.

17:27.400 --> 17:28.600
You mustn't miss it.

17:34.560 --> 17:36.280
You remind me of my daughter.

17:40.840 --> 17:41.680
I do?

17:42.480 --> 17:43.320
Yes.

17:56.920 --> 18:00.160
I thought we agreed
you weren't going to the party.

18:03.360 --> 18:04.960
I changed my mind, Mom.

18:06.400 --> 18:08.000
I think you should stay home.

18:08.880 --> 18:09.960
It's for your own sake.

18:10.040 --> 18:15.280
If I don't go, it's for your sake.

18:16.720 --> 18:17.640
You know it is.

18:18.800 --> 18:20.560
It's just a party, Mom...

18:21.320 --> 18:23.320
not the end of the world.

18:25.040 --> 18:26.320
Will there be a lot of boys?

18:27.200 --> 18:30.000
The boys from school are coming.

18:31.560 --> 18:33.680
Are you going to drink and smoke?

18:34.240 --> 18:36.800
Maybe they are, but I'm not, am I?

18:38.080 --> 18:39.080
Mom...

18:40.920 --> 18:42.440
-You're wearing makeup?
-Stop it.

18:44.960 --> 18:45.960
Mom!

18:49.880 --> 18:52.400
Mom, you have to support me.

18:54.440 --> 18:57.720
-You always make me feel like a freak.
-You're not a freak.

18:57.800 --> 19:00.240
-But you make me feel like one.
-But you're not.

19:00.320 --> 19:01.240
No, I'm not.

19:01.320 --> 19:05.200
I'm going to the party,
and I won't stay out late.

19:16.400 --> 19:17.920
