30:38.680 --> 30:39.520
Everything?

30:42.400 --> 30:44.080
Are you and Martin a couple?

30:46.320 --> 30:47.520
You are, aren't you?

30:49.360 --> 30:50.480
I don't know.

30:52.520 --> 30:53.440
Strange.

30:55.920 --> 30:59.040
Yeah. But he isn't like you.

31:01.760 --> 31:02.800
What am I like?

31:03.240 --> 31:04.280
You're honest.

31:06.040 --> 31:07.240
Is that a good thing?

31:08.720 --> 31:09.720
It's pretty good.

31:11.360 --> 31:12.200
Very good.

31:13.160 --> 31:14.200
Hi.

31:15.640 --> 31:18.080
Hi. Beatrice is looking for Martin.

31:18.600 --> 31:19.680
Have you seen him?

31:23.640 --> 31:24.480
No.

31:26.480 --> 31:29.280
Okay. He must be in his room, then.

31:38.200 --> 31:39.240
Well?

31:40.000 --> 31:40.960
What?

32:02.640 --> 32:03.480
Hi.

32:04.120 --> 32:05.320
Where have you been?

32:10.040 --> 32:10.880
I...

32:12.160 --> 32:13.160
I've been...

32:15.080 --> 32:18.360
-in the basement.
-Strange first date, isn't it?

32:19.920 --> 32:20.760
What?

32:21.480 --> 32:23.600
You and Simone have been hanging out.

32:24.600 --> 32:25.720
No.

32:26.960 --> 32:28.760
-It's pretty obvious.
-No, listen.

32:28.840 --> 32:32.520
I'm trying to find out
what the hell's going on in this house.

32:32.600 --> 32:35.240
-It's so obvious.
-This isn't about us.

32:35.320 --> 32:38.280
-It sure isn't.
-No, it isn't. It's just that I...

32:39.320 --> 32:42.360
I feel like I'm losing all of you.

32:42.440 --> 32:43.640
-All of us?
-Yes.

32:45.480 --> 32:46.480
Right.

32:52.560 --> 32:55.960
Maybe Martin and Beatrice
aren't a real couple.

32:57.120 --> 32:58.480
Maybe they're just having sex.

33:02.240 --> 33:03.080
Yeah.

33:03.560 --> 33:05.640
-Did you ever have sex before the rain?
-No.

33:06.440 --> 33:07.880
-Before the rain...
-No!

33:08.760 --> 33:10.240
Don't you want to try it?

33:11.600 --> 33:14.520
I'm trying to figure out
whether to stay or to leave this place.

33:14.600 --> 33:15.920
-Okay?
-Yeah, okay.

33:18.400 --> 33:19.840
It seems natural to the others.

33:20.400 --> 33:22.080
Why do you ask?

33:22.160 --> 33:23.920
It's not a weird thing to talk about.

33:26.280 --> 33:28.840
It is with my little brother.

33:29.920 --> 33:33.280
Oh, okay. Maybe you should
talk to Martin about it.

33:33.760 --> 33:35.320
Cut it out!

33:39.400 --> 33:40.600
But don't you want to try?

33:53.120 --> 33:56.320
<i>-We're going to find my gun and leave.</i>
<i>-Why do you get to decide that?</i>

33:56.400 --> 34:01.240
I don't, Patrick.
This place is coming between us.

34:01.640 --> 34:03.840
-There's something wrong here.
-No, there isn't.

34:03.920 --> 34:07.400
Okay, fine, but we're still
in a quarantine zone.

34:07.480 --> 34:10.719
-Wasn't the plan to get out of it?
-What about the Apollon guy?

34:11.360 --> 34:13.840
-What?
-There's a guy from Apollon here.

34:13.920 --> 34:15.400
What does that mean?

34:15.480 --> 34:17.639
He was about to inject Rasmus
with something.

34:18.159 --> 34:19.199
He knows something.

34:19.280 --> 34:21.800
We'll find the answers somewhere else.

34:21.880 --> 34:23.840
We can't leave until Rasmus is better.

34:23.920 --> 34:25.320
But it's not safe here.

34:26.320 --> 34:28.960
-I vote to stay.
-Me too.

34:29.040 --> 34:29.880
For sure.

34:30.719 --> 34:32.320
-Good.
-Yes.

34:33.520 --> 34:35.360
Looks like you're going alone.

34:35.440 --> 34:36.360
You're crazy.

34:38.000 --> 34:40.880
Why don't you just leave
and we'll come later?

34:41.920 --> 34:43.159
What's happening to you?

34:43.239 --> 34:45.840
Why can't you just stay here with us?

34:45.920 --> 34:46.800
He can't.

34:48.880 --> 34:51.400
-He can't stand not being in charge.
-Bea...

34:52.320 --> 34:53.760
He'd rather be alone.

35:00.480 --> 35:02.360
-Lea, are you coming?
-Sure.

35:02.960 --> 35:04.040
Where are you going?

35:04.560 --> 35:06.920
We'll see you at the dinner.

35:08.160 --> 35:09.480
-Yeah.
-Come.

35:13.880 --> 35:14.880
Don't you see it?

35:17.960 --> 35:18.880
Martin...

35:24.720 --> 35:25.560
Hey.

35:34.680 --> 35:35.720
This is so wrong.

35:36.600 --> 35:37.800
It's his own choice.

36:05.840 --> 36:06.680
<i>Hello?</i>

36:08.000 --> 36:09.040
Is someone there?

36:13.640 --> 36:14.480
Hello?

36:39.000 --> 36:41.600
<i>Dear God... you need to help me.</i>

36:44.320 --> 36:49.120
I don't know what happened,
but you need to help me.

37:37.240 --> 37:38.480
<i>-Lea?</i>
-Mom?

37:39.480 --> 37:40.920
<i>Lea, can you hear me?</i>

37:41.760 --> 37:44.600
Mom, they...

37:46.760 --> 37:47.880
<i>Don't be sad.</i>

37:49.240 --> 37:51.440
<i>-I'll come pick you up.</i>
-Mom, don't leave.

37:51.520 --> 37:53.880
<i>-I'm leaving right now. I...</i>
-Don't go outside.

38:04.680 --> 38:06.280
My mom...

38:06.960 --> 38:09.400
I killed my mother.

38:09.840 --> 38:11.440
You lost your mother...

38:12.640 --> 38:14.400
but you didn't kill her.

38:17.680 --> 38:20.040
We all lost someone before we came here.

38:20.680 --> 38:25.360
Little Lea, you didn't kill anyone. Okay?

38:25.720 --> 38:26.720
Yes.

38:28.400 --> 38:29.960
Did you lose someone, too?

38:31.240 --> 38:32.080
Did you?

38:34.320 --> 38:35.160
A...

38:37.280 --> 38:38.960
A daughter and a grandchild.

38:40.920 --> 38:41.920
Where are they?

38:43.520 --> 38:44.360
Here.

38:47.440 --> 38:48.560
They're right here.

39:37.560 --> 39:41.720
Welcome to this,
our traditional monthly celebration.

39:42.600 --> 39:45.920
As usual, we will observe
absolute silence...

39:47.000 --> 39:48.600
both to honor the meal...

39:49.400 --> 39:56.080
and to open up to this boundless love
that will flow through us from the meal,

39:56.520 --> 39:58.160
dissolving us as individuals.

39:59.280 --> 40:01.200
We are each other.

40:01.800 --> 40:03.640
We are in each other.

40:04.560 --> 40:07.200
We are nothing without each other.

40:07.280 --> 40:08.240
Now eat.

40:08.680 --> 40:09.880
I hope you like it.

41:08.560 --> 41:10.200
I hope you all appreciated the meal.

41:11.280 --> 41:17.240
Now it's time to find the next person
who will gratify us with their body...

41:18.200 --> 41:20.440
thus getting eternal life.

41:22.560 --> 41:23.920
What is he talking about?

41:24.920 --> 41:25.880
What is this?

41:31.920 --> 41:33.560
Did we eat a human being?

41:40.200 --> 41:41.360
There now.

41:42.200 --> 41:43.080
Karen?

41:43.480 --> 41:49.000
You've been fortunate
to experience ultimate love.

41:53.480 --> 41:54.560
We want to leave.

41:54.960 --> 41:57.040
Sit down.

41:59.480 --> 42:02.840
Once you've partaken of the meal,
you're part of the community.

42:03.280 --> 42:06.960
The one who finds a flower
in the wrapper is the chosen one...

42:07.640 --> 42:09.560
and will come to the basement directly...

42:10.440 --> 42:11.920
-to give their life to us.
-Hey!

42:12.600 --> 42:14.640
-Martin.
-Stop!

42:15.840 --> 42:18.120
Step away! Step away from him!

42:18.600 --> 42:20.040
You can't stop this now.

42:21.200 --> 42:22.720
Your friends have to stay here...

42:23.160 --> 42:25.520
-Martin?
-...until we've found a flower.

42:25.600 --> 42:26.440
Martin?

42:28.600 --> 42:29.440
Martin?

42:30.960 --> 42:31.800
I'll start.

42:44.040 --> 42:45.120
Go ahead.

43:19.040 --> 43:21.120
I think we've found the chosen one.

43:26.640 --> 43:28.960
-What?
-Lea, sit down.

43:29.040 --> 43:31.280
-Shut up and sit down!
-What is this?

43:33.760 --> 43:34.840
What is this?

43:40.200 --> 43:41.160
Karen?

43:43.080 --> 43:45.720
You took the wrong one.

43:45.800 --> 43:47.280
-Karen?
-It's mine.

43:53.320 --> 43:56.280
-No!
-Thank you all for...

43:58.680 --> 44:03.040
for allowing me to become one of you.

44:05.000 --> 44:07.120
It's a huge honor for me to...

44:09.440 --> 44:11.360
to live on in you.

44:13.040 --> 44:14.040
Thank you.

44:14.120 --> 44:17.040
No! I need you.

44:17.800 --> 44:20.400
-No.
-Yes!

44:20.480 --> 44:21.800
Come, come, come.

44:23.600 --> 44:25.040
I need you.

44:26.520 --> 44:29.000
-You must live.
-No.

44:29.080 --> 44:30.720
You must live!

44:35.800 --> 44:36.840
Please let go.

44:39.000 --> 44:41.240
No!

44:47.080 --> 44:49.160
All has been revealed now.

44:49.240 --> 44:52.360
You can either go or stay.
Do as you wish.

44:53.040 --> 44:55.960
But you won't find
a better place than this.

44:56.040 --> 44:57.600
Come. We're leaving.

45:12.360 --> 45:14.880
Give us our backpacks and my gun.

45:19.240 --> 45:20.480
What was in that syringe?

45:20.560 --> 45:21.480
Simone.

45:21.840 --> 45:22.960
You know something.

45:26.240 --> 45:28.040
You know something. Tell me!

45:31.000 --> 45:31.960
Did you know my dad?

45:32.040 --> 45:33.280
Frederik Andersen?

45:34.920 --> 45:35.760
Yes.

45:36.720 --> 45:37.840
We did it.

45:39.000 --> 45:40.600
We destroyed the world.

45:41.040 --> 45:43.520
But it will be better when...

45:44.360 --> 45:46.200
Let's go, Simone.

45:46.280 --> 45:48.320
We have to go, okay?

45:51.080 --> 45:52.360
Simone, come.

45:55.920 --> 45:57.080
You have to go now.

45:58.680 --> 46:01.200
What? No.

46:01.280 --> 46:04.640
You're stuck in the past.

46:06.200 --> 46:07.920
She has the right to know the truth.

46:09.280 --> 46:12.200
We have to stand by what we've done.

46:12.280 --> 46:13.160
Go now.

46:15.200 --> 46:16.040
Go.

46:17.400 --> 46:18.760
You're on your own now.

46:19.440 --> 46:21.160
You cannot leave me out here.

46:28.480 --> 46:29.800
What do we do now?

46:31.120 --> 46:35.760
I mean... you know best.
So, what's the plan, Martin?

46:41.040 --> 46:43.200
You want to know what's in the syringe?

46:43.280 --> 46:46.560
We thought we would save everyone
with this. Instead we killed them all.

46:47.600 --> 46:48.440
No!

47:09.000 --> 47:10.800
Let's get out of this fucking zone.

47:13.600 --> 47:15.520
But we'll stop by Apollon first.

